  "body": "  How many 5-letter words can you make using the eight letters through ? How many contain no repeated letters?    By now it should be no surprise that there are words, and words without repeated letters. The new piece here is that we are actually counting functions. For the first problem, we are counting all functions from to . The numbers in the domain represent the position of the letter in the word, the codomain represents the letter that could be assigned to that position. If we ask for no repeated letters, we are asking for injective functions.  If and are any sets with and , then the number of functions is and the number of injections is . So if you can represent your counting problem as a function counting problem, most of the work is done.   "
