  "title": "",
  "body": "handshakes  Use induction to prove that if people all shake hands with each other, that the total number of handshakes is .   We have already proved this without using induction, but looking at it inductively sheds light onto the problem (and is fun).  The question you need to answer to complete the inductive step is, how many new handshakes take place when a person enters the room. Why does adding this give you the correct formula?  "
