  "body": "handshakes connection to graphs  If 10 people each shake hands with each other, how many handshakes took place? What does this question have to do with graph theory?   This is asking for the number of edges in . Each vertex (person) has degree (shook hands with) 9 (people). So the sum of the degrees is . However, the degrees count each edge (handshake) twice, so there are 45 edges in the graph. That is how many handshakes took place.  "
